headline: Cash Still King: One in Three Homes Bought with Cash in 2025
summary: Nearly one in three homes sold in the first half of 2025 were bought entirely with cash, according to a new analysis from Realtor.com®. The report highlights how cash buyers, ranging from equity-rich households to investors and second-home purchasers, continue to wield outsize influence in today's housing market.
